          "tool_call_id": "chatcmpl-tool-8d2e966c2128d2e6",
          "content": "{\"query\": \"Llama 4 Maverick experts number 8 experts\", \"top_k\": [{\"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_xTA17bKjF4\", \"title\": \"Llama 4 Maverick - Everything You Need To Know - YouTube\", \"content\": \"... Llama 4 #Maverick, a 17-billion-parameter model utilizing a mixture-of-experts (MoE) architecture with 128 experts. This design enables Maverick\", \"score\": 0.99997663, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=12lAM-xPvu8\", \"title\": \"Llama 4 Maverick 400B: First Real-World TEST - YouTube\", \"content\": \"Live REASONING TEST of Llama 4 Maverick. Lama 4 Maverick is a 400B parameter model, with 128 experts and 17B active parameters.\", \"score\": 0.9996724, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://huggingface.co/blog/llama4-release\", \"title\": \"Welcome Llama 4 Maverick & Scout on Hugging Face\", \"content\": \"We are incredibly excited to welcome the next generation of large language models from Meta to the Hugging Face Hub: Llama 4 Maverick (~400B) and Llama 4 Scout (~109B)! The Llama 4 models were pre-trained with a context length of 256K. The Instruct models were fine-tuned to support much larger context lengths: 1M in the large 128 experts version (Maverick), and 10M (!) for the 16 experts version (Scout). As a way to reduce memory requirements, Llama 4 uses chunked attention in the layers that work with traditional RoPE positional encodings (three out of 4 decoder layers). To address this problem, Llama 4 uses a scaled softmax, which the model refers to as temperature tuning. model_id = \\\"meta-llama/Llama-4-Maverick-17B-128E-Instruct\\\". Make sure to check the model cards on the repos (Llama 4 Maverick (~400B) and Llama 4 Scout (~109B)) for detailed usage instructions, including multimodal examples, specific prompt formats (like system prompts), quantization details, and advanced configuration options!\", \"score\": 0.9996018, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://vllm.ai/blog/llama4\", \"title\": \"Llama 4 in vLLM | vLLM Blog\", \"content\": \"We're excited to announce that vLLM now supports the Llama 4 herd of models: **Scout** (17B-16E) and **Maverick** (17B-128E). You can run these powerful long-context, natively multi-modal (up to 8-10 images with good results), mixture-of-experts models in vLLM today by updating to version v0.8.3 or later:. We also recommend checking out the demo from the Meta team showcasing the 1M long context capability with vLLM. Using 8xH100, vLLM can serve Scout with 1M context and Maverick with about 430K. VLLM_DISABLE_COMPILE_CACHE=1 vllm serve meta-llama/Llama-4-Scout-17B-16E-Instruct \\\\ --tensor-parallel-size 8 \\\\ --max-model-len 1000000 --override-generation-config='{\\\"attn_temperature_tuning\\\": true}'. VLLM_DISABLE_COMPILE_CACHE=1 vllm serve meta-llama/Llama-4-Maverick-17B-128E-Instruct-FP8 \\\\ --tensor-parallel-size 8 \\\\ --max-model-len 430000'. VLLM_DISABLE_COMPILE_CACHE=1 vllm serve meta-llama/Llama-4-Scout-17B-16E-Instruct \\\\ --tensor-parallel-size 8 \\\\ --max-model-len 3600000'. VLLM_DISABLE_COMPILE_CACHE=1 vllm serve meta-llama/Llama-4-Maverick-17B-128E-Instruct-FP8 \\\\ --tensor-parallel-size 8 --max-model-len 1000000'. While more performance enhancements are on the way, we believe the Llama 4 models' efficient architecture and relatively small size make them practical for scaled usage today. Llama 4\\u2019s model architecture is particularly well-suited for efficient long-context inference, thanks to features like:.\", \"score\": 0.99957937, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/llama-4-independent-benchmarks-maverick-402b-total-b4bmc\", \"title\": \"Llama 4 independent benchmarks: Maverick (402B total, 17B active ...\", \"content\": \"# Llama 4 independent benchmarks: Maverick (402B total, 17B active) beats Claude 3.7 Sonnet, trails DeepSeek V3 but more efficient. We have independently benchmarked Scout and Maverick as scoring 36 and 49 in Artificial Analysis Intelligence Index respectively. We have independently benchmarked Scout and Maverick as scoring 36 and 49 in Artificial Analysis Intelligence Index respectively. \\u27a4 The Llama 4 \\u2018herd\\u2019 includes Scout, Maverick and Behemoth; all are large Mixture of Experts (MoE) models - the first time that Meta has released MoE models. \\u27a4 Behemoth (2T total, 288B active) is not being released today but Meta discloses that it was used for co-distillation into Scout and Maverick. \\u27a4 Pricing: We\\u2019re tracking 6 providers and are benchmarking a median price $0.24/$0.77 per million input/output tokens for Maverick, and $0.15/$0.4 for Scout lower than DeepSeek v3 and >10X cheaper than OpenAI\\u2019s leading GPT-4o endpoint. GLM-5 leads the Artificial Analysis Intelligence Index amongst open weights models.\", \"score\": 0.99945146, \"raw_content\": null}]}"
